WEBVTT

00:07.960 --> 00:10.240
[Police radio chatter]

00:10.280 --> 00:14.880
♪

00:14.920 --> 00:16.920
[Police radio chatter continues]

00:16.960 --> 00:22.720
♪

00:22.760 --> 00:25.600
No!

00:25.640 --> 00:28.400
[Engine revving]

00:28.440 --> 00:32.400
♪

00:32.440 --> 00:36.480
[Breathing heavily]

00:36.520 --> 00:44.240
♪

00:44.280 --> 00:46.080
[Siren wails in distance]

00:46.120 --> 00:48.200
[Police radio chatter]

00:48.240 --> 00:50.440
-Get back!
-No.

00:50.480 --> 00:52.440
I just want to see him.
I just want to see my son.
-I'm sorry, Miss.

00:52.480 --> 00:55.360
I want to fucking see my son.
I want to see Jamie.

00:55.400 --> 00:57.320
I just want to see Jamie.
I just want --

00:57.360 --> 00:59.080
I just want to see him
for a second.

00:59.120 --> 01:01.000
Is he in here?
-Come on, come on. Let's go.

01:01.040 --> 01:03.280
-I just want to see him.
Please, please, please.
-Sorry, no.

01:03.320 --> 01:05.080
Hey, get your fucking hands
off her!

01:05.120 --> 01:06.760
Get your hands off her!
-I just want to see my Jamie.

01:06.800 --> 01:08.800
What's wrong with you?
Hey, hey.

01:08.840 --> 01:10.880
It's okay. You can't.
You can't see him right now.

01:10.920 --> 01:12.600
[Gasps] I have to see him.
I have to see him.

01:12.640 --> 01:14.480
He's my son. He's my son.
-This isn't how you want --

01:14.520 --> 01:15.960
This isn't how you want
to remember him. Trust me.

01:16.000 --> 01:18.760
Not here, not like this.
Trust me.

01:18.800 --> 01:21.880
No. [Cries]

01:21.920 --> 01:24.760
I have to see him.
Please let me see him.

01:24.800 --> 01:27.280
[Sobbing]

01:27.320 --> 01:29.560
[Police radio chatter]

01:29.600 --> 01:36.760
♪

01:36.800 --> 01:43.920
♪

01:43.960 --> 01:47.480
[Indistinct conversations]

01:47.520 --> 01:56.960
♪

01:57.000 --> 02:06.720
♪

02:06.760 --> 02:09.400
[Footsteps approaching]

02:09.440 --> 02:15.200
♪

02:15.240 --> 02:16.560
[Sighs]

02:16.600 --> 02:19.160
-Frank.
-Where is he?

02:19.200 --> 02:20.680
They've taken him in
to theatre.

02:20.720 --> 02:22.080
How bad is he?

02:22.120 --> 02:24.160
It's bad, but they say
he'll be okay.

02:24.200 --> 02:25.800
He's not gonna die
or anything.

02:25.840 --> 02:28.160
Did he say
what happened?

02:28.200 --> 02:31.800
Just that they tried to kill
them and that Jamie was dead.

02:31.840 --> 02:33.080
Is it true?

02:33.120 --> 02:35.200
Yeah.

02:35.240 --> 02:37.080
Why?

02:37.120 --> 02:39.720
I don't know.

02:39.760 --> 02:41.560
But I'm gonna
find out.

02:41.600 --> 02:47.600
♪

02:47.640 --> 02:53.840
♪

02:53.880 --> 02:56.400
Probably won't let us have
the body for a few days.

02:56.440 --> 02:58.720
The body?

02:58.760 --> 03:00.840
Jamie.

03:00.880 --> 03:02.680
You know what I mean.

03:05.360 --> 03:07.520
I didn't even want him
driving tonight.

03:07.560 --> 03:10.040
What?

03:10.080 --> 03:11.840
I said that.

03:14.760 --> 03:17.320
I said he shouldn't be driving,
but you said let him go.

03:18.600 --> 03:21.080
[Scoffs]

03:21.120 --> 03:23.240
I didn't want him
having his own car.

03:25.640 --> 03:28.160
What --

03:28.200 --> 03:30.880
You think
I wanted this to happen?

03:30.920 --> 03:33.800
If you hadn't given him
his own car,

03:33.840 --> 03:35.440
he wouldn't have
been there.

03:35.480 --> 03:37.960
I cared about him just as
fucking much as you did.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.680
Just as much.

03:40.720 --> 03:44.480
♪

03:44.520 --> 03:45.600
[Keypad beeping]

03:45.640 --> 03:47.880
[Lock disengages]

03:47.920 --> 03:56.960
♪

03:57.000 --> 03:59.240
[Sirens wailing]

03:59.280 --> 04:05.280
♪

04:05.320 --> 04:08.280
Frank.
You got a name yet, Frank?

04:08.320 --> 04:09.960
You got a name?

04:10.000 --> 04:11.320
-Jimmy.
-You got a name?

04:11.360 --> 04:12.800
We are all in bits
over Jamie, okay?

04:12.840 --> 04:14.600
We're not gonna rest until
this is fucking settled.

04:14.640 --> 04:15.960
But who did this? Who'd attack
our family like this?

04:16.000 --> 04:17.760
Who the fuck
would do this, Frank?

04:17.800 --> 04:19.440
We're working on that right now,
okay? We will get a name.

04:19.480 --> 04:22.440
We'll get names.
Whoever did this is dead.

04:22.480 --> 04:30.160
♪

04:30.200 --> 04:32.600
They have anything to say
for themselves?

04:32.640 --> 04:33.920
Fuck all.

04:33.960 --> 04:37.240
[Siren wails in distance]

04:37.280 --> 04:38.720
[Engine idling]

04:38.760 --> 04:46.560
♪

04:46.600 --> 04:47.640
[Car door opens]

04:51.320 --> 04:54.120
-You alright, pet?
-Yeah.

04:54.160 --> 04:56.080
What did the police say?

04:56.120 --> 04:58.640
Not much.
Just took a statement.

04:58.680 --> 05:00.880
They give you any idea
who they think did it?

05:00.920 --> 05:02.120
No.

05:04.200 --> 05:06.480
How are Jimmy
and Amanda doing?

05:06.520 --> 05:08.680
It's not gonna be easy
for them.

05:08.720 --> 05:10.760
Especially Jimmy.

05:10.800 --> 05:13.480
He'll have his hands full
with Amanda.

05:13.520 --> 05:16.880
♪

05:16.920 --> 05:18.680
When a mother
loses a child,

05:18.720 --> 05:23.520
it's like a fucking madness
takes over you.

05:26.120 --> 05:27.880
I know.

05:30.360 --> 05:33.160
You have to be there
for your brother, Mikey.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.200
Yeah, I know that.

05:35.240 --> 05:39.160
♪

05:39.200 --> 05:40.920
Frank: What are youse
hearing out there?

05:40.960 --> 05:43.200
Dotser: These two are saying
Caolan Moore set it up

05:43.240 --> 05:44.840
'cause of all the shit
between him and Eric.

05:44.880 --> 05:46.200
I thought
that was settled.

05:46.240 --> 05:47.440
Sorry, who's saying
it was Caolan Moore?

05:47.480 --> 05:48.720
Just some of the lads
we were talking to.

05:48.760 --> 05:49.720
That's all.

05:49.760 --> 05:51.200
Well, that's bollocks.

05:51.240 --> 05:53.200
We sorted
all that shit out.

05:53.240 --> 05:54.840
Just telling you what I heard,
Frank.

05:54.880 --> 05:58.800
Well, if it was Moore,
he's a fucking snake.

05:58.840 --> 06:00.280
Where is he now?

06:00.320 --> 06:02.320
Gone underground if he's got
a brain in his head.

06:02.360 --> 06:04.320
Find out fucking where.

06:04.360 --> 06:05.840
Jimmy, we don't even know
it was him yet, okay?

06:05.880 --> 06:07.440
Not for sure.

06:07.480 --> 06:09.960
I want you two
back out there, okay?

06:10.000 --> 06:11.640
You hear anything,
call Dotser.

06:11.680 --> 06:13.680
Yeah.

06:13.720 --> 06:16.640
Sorry about Jamie,
Jimmy.

06:16.680 --> 06:19.040
This is fucked up.

06:19.080 --> 06:21.040
Likewise.

06:21.080 --> 06:23.480
Yeah. Thanks.

06:23.520 --> 06:26.760
[Telephone rings]

06:26.800 --> 06:29.560
If it was Caolan Moore,
we need to find out

06:29.600 --> 06:31.240
if Eamon Cunningham
okay'd this.

06:31.280 --> 06:32.560
No, I don't give a fuck
who okay'd it, Frank.

06:32.600 --> 06:34.080
Moore's getting his,
and that's fucking it.

06:34.120 --> 06:35.720
I know you're raging, Jimmy.
We all are.

06:35.760 --> 06:37.560
But if Eamon's behind this,
we've got much bigger problems

06:37.600 --> 06:40.600
than what happens
to fucking Caolan Moore.

06:40.640 --> 06:41.960
I just need a little bit of time
to find out

06:42.000 --> 06:43.840
what the fuck's
going on.

06:43.880 --> 06:45.960
The last thing I need
is you losing the head

06:46.000 --> 06:48.160
and making things worse.
-Worse?

06:48.200 --> 06:50.520
Worse, Frank?

06:50.560 --> 06:54.160
Yeah, you just need to
calm down, okay?

06:54.200 --> 06:56.560
Call Doyler.
Get a vibe from him.

06:56.600 --> 07:00.160
Tell him
we want to see Eamon.

07:00.200 --> 07:05.280
Just...go home,
take care of your family.

07:05.320 --> 07:07.560
Let me sort this out.

07:07.600 --> 07:09.560
[Sighs]

07:09.600 --> 07:13.760
♪

07:13.800 --> 07:15.640
[Pounding on door]

07:22.960 --> 07:25.320
[Dog barks in distance]

07:30.200 --> 07:32.080
Tell me exactly
what happened.

07:32.120 --> 07:33.600
It won't do any good,
Amanda.

07:33.640 --> 07:35.280
I don't care.

07:35.320 --> 07:38.120
I want to know.

07:38.160 --> 07:40.920
We were in the car park
at the gym.

07:40.960 --> 07:43.480
Some lad ran up to us
and started shooting.

07:43.520 --> 07:46.800
No, before that. What --
What happened before that?

07:46.840 --> 07:49.320
Like, w-when --
when you were in the car,

07:49.360 --> 07:52.040
what -- what -- what
were you talking about?

07:52.080 --> 07:56.280
Uh, he asked me
about Jimmy,

07:56.320 --> 07:58.560
wanted to know
what he was like as a kid.

07:58.600 --> 08:00.440
That kinda thing.
-What did you say?

08:00.480 --> 08:02.240
You know, the truth --

08:02.280 --> 08:06.120
that he was funny
and a bit of a prick.

08:06.160 --> 08:08.680
But that he always
looked out for me.

08:08.720 --> 08:13.560
After that, we spoke about Anna
for a while, and that was it.

08:13.600 --> 08:15.640
T-Then what?

08:15.680 --> 08:17.440
We arrived at the gym,
we got out the car,

08:17.480 --> 08:19.720
and he was laughing.

08:19.760 --> 08:21.760
J-Jamie was laughing

08:21.800 --> 08:24.360
'cause he'd seen Viking
had a flat tire.

08:24.400 --> 08:27.240
He took a photo of it
and sent it to Viking to --

08:27.280 --> 08:29.560
to wind him up,
and then Viking came,

08:29.600 --> 08:32.280
and we realized that a puncture
had been done deliberately.

08:34.280 --> 08:37.120
And then that's when
the shooting happened.

08:39.160 --> 08:42.600
Did Jamie...

08:42.640 --> 08:46.280
say anything
after he was shot?

08:46.320 --> 08:49.360
♪

08:49.400 --> 08:51.360
He was gone.

08:51.400 --> 08:59.160
♪

08:59.200 --> 09:02.240
So, uh, the last thing
he was doing was just, like,

09:02.280 --> 09:04.920
laughing
and messing around?

09:04.960 --> 09:07.120
Yeah.

09:07.160 --> 09:09.200
Well, at least he wasn't scared,
you know?

09:09.240 --> 09:12.920
Like, he didn't, um --

09:12.960 --> 09:15.520
he didn't suffer
or anything.

09:15.560 --> 09:17.400
No.

09:17.440 --> 09:19.960
That --

09:20.000 --> 09:22.600
That's something,
you know?

09:22.640 --> 09:24.240
Yeah.

09:26.240 --> 09:30.600
[Breathes shakily]

09:30.640 --> 09:33.120
[Sniffles]

09:33.160 --> 09:35.200
[Breathes shakily]

09:35.240 --> 09:37.800
[Bird calling]

09:37.840 --> 09:40.040
[Water running]

09:40.080 --> 09:44.080
♪

09:44.120 --> 09:45.440
[Knock on door]

09:45.480 --> 09:47.480
Anthony: Mam,
the police are here.

09:47.520 --> 09:53.480
♪

09:53.520 --> 09:56.320
As your Family Liaison Officer,
I'll keep you informed

09:56.360 --> 09:58.320
about the Garda
investigation.

09:58.360 --> 10:00.680
So, if you have any questions or
if there's anything I can do --

10:00.720 --> 10:02.920
When can I see my son?

10:02.960 --> 10:05.400
They wouldn't let me see him
last night.

10:05.440 --> 10:07.640
That's because it was still
a live crime scene, and --

10:07.680 --> 10:09.240
She's his mother.

10:09.280 --> 10:11.040
She should be allowed
to see him.

10:11.080 --> 10:12.640
And she will be.

10:12.680 --> 10:14.240
But Jamie has to be moved
to the morgue,

10:14.280 --> 10:16.640
and then there'll
be a postmortem.

10:16.680 --> 10:18.640
So, when?

10:18.680 --> 10:20.800
When can I see him?

10:20.840 --> 10:24.080
I can't say exactly.
Not yet.

10:24.120 --> 10:26.720
So, what use are you
to us, then?

10:26.760 --> 10:29.440
Like I said, I can answer
any questions

10:29.480 --> 10:32.280
you have about
the investigation.

10:32.320 --> 10:36.200
The only question I have
is, when can I see him?

10:36.240 --> 10:38.120
Come back
when you know that.

10:38.160 --> 10:40.200
'Cause it's the only thing
I'm interested in.

10:42.320 --> 10:45.440
I'll let you know
when I hear anything.

10:45.480 --> 10:47.480
Yeah.

10:47.520 --> 10:53.200
♪

10:53.240 --> 10:55.840
[Sighs]

10:55.880 --> 10:58.480
This is a big
fucking mistake.

10:58.520 --> 11:02.000
He's not gonna do anything,
not here.

11:02.040 --> 11:12.000
♪

11:12.040 --> 11:13.560
[Door closes]

11:13.600 --> 11:14.920
[Sighs]

11:14.960 --> 11:17.280
[Clears throat]

11:19.120 --> 11:21.640
I have a flight to catch.
There's a car downstairs.

11:21.680 --> 11:23.280
We can talk on the way
to the airport.

11:23.320 --> 11:25.760
I thought we were
doing this here, no?

11:25.800 --> 11:27.680
I told you,
I have a flight to catch.

11:27.720 --> 11:29.080
And it's just Frank.

11:29.120 --> 11:32.080
You're not coming, Dotser.

11:32.120 --> 11:34.480
You ready?

11:34.520 --> 11:37.840
Look --
come, don't come.

11:37.880 --> 11:40.320
Your choice.
I don't care.

11:40.360 --> 11:50.360
♪

11:50.400 --> 11:58.800
♪

11:58.840 --> 12:01.240
[Car door closes]

12:01.280 --> 12:09.240
♪

12:09.280 --> 12:11.440
[Engine starts]

12:11.480 --> 12:20.440
♪

12:20.480 --> 12:29.280
♪

12:29.320 --> 12:31.680
This isn't the way
to the airport.

12:34.240 --> 12:36.680
We have a stop-off
first.

12:36.720 --> 12:46.640
♪

12:46.680 --> 12:56.680
♪

12:56.720 --> 13:01.360
♪

13:01.400 --> 13:03.760
[Car door closes]

13:06.280 --> 13:07.560
[Car door closes]

13:07.600 --> 13:10.400
I take it
you know who this is.

13:10.440 --> 13:12.280
Yeah.

13:12.320 --> 13:14.240
You asked me to sort things
between him and your lot,

13:14.280 --> 13:17.320
and as soon as I do,
you go and screw it all up.

13:17.360 --> 13:19.160
That's bollocks, Eamon.

13:19.200 --> 13:20.800
Whatever you've heard,
it's wrong.

13:20.840 --> 13:23.440
Shut the fuck up.

13:23.480 --> 13:26.600
Hours after I talked to Caolan
like you asked,

13:26.640 --> 13:29.760
your idiot son goes
and shoots one of his lads.

13:32.200 --> 13:34.400
Eric said he had nothing
to do with that.

13:34.440 --> 13:36.960
Then he's fucking lying,
because he was seen.

13:37.000 --> 13:39.520
He was seen doing it,
Frank.

13:39.560 --> 13:42.000
He showed up at some restaurant
earlier, mouthing off,

13:42.040 --> 13:43.520
and when that
didn't go his way,

13:43.560 --> 13:45.760
he followed them to their gaff
and started shooting,

13:45.800 --> 13:50.600
so all this shit now,
that's on Eric.

13:50.640 --> 13:54.120
Unless, of course...

13:54.160 --> 13:57.160
you were behind it,
too, Frank,

13:57.200 --> 13:59.360
and you want
a fucking war.

13:59.400 --> 14:04.520
♪

14:04.560 --> 14:07.400
No.

14:07.440 --> 14:09.760
No, I thought it was sorted.

14:11.800 --> 14:14.880
I swear, Eamon,
I knew nothing about this.

14:16.160 --> 14:17.840
[Clicks tongue]

14:19.280 --> 14:24.280
Viking getting shot,
he brought that on himself.

14:24.320 --> 14:33.720
♪

14:33.760 --> 14:37.080
That's for Jimmy.

14:37.120 --> 14:39.560
What happened to his young lad
was a mistake,

14:39.600 --> 14:43.520
and Caolan's offered to pay
compo to put that right.

14:43.560 --> 14:45.840
By rights, Viking
should be paying it.

14:45.880 --> 14:48.920
Now...

14:48.960 --> 14:51.120
this a fucking end to it,
Frank?

14:53.640 --> 14:54.840
Yeah.

14:54.880 --> 14:57.600
I hope so.

14:57.640 --> 15:00.320
'Cause next time, you and I
will not be talking.

15:00.360 --> 15:06.920
♪

15:06.960 --> 15:08.640
[Car door opens, engine starts,
car doors close]

15:08.680 --> 15:18.680
♪

15:18.720 --> 15:21.760
[Indistinct talking on TV]

15:21.800 --> 15:23.920
Your milk. Here.

15:23.960 --> 15:25.160
Thanks.

15:25.200 --> 15:26.840
You're welcome.

15:26.880 --> 15:30.400
Now, don't forget
your lunch box, Anna.

15:31.880 --> 15:34.200
[Cellphone chimes]

15:45.480 --> 15:48.280
♪

15:48.320 --> 15:51.920
[Spoon stirring]

15:51.960 --> 15:56.440
♪

15:56.480 --> 15:59.760
The victim has been named
locally as Jamie Kinsella.

15:59.800 --> 16:01.560
The 17-year-old
is not believed

16:01.600 --> 16:04.240
to have any involvement
in criminality.

16:04.280 --> 16:06.440
At the time of the shooting,
he was in the company

16:06.480 --> 16:08.440
of two male relatives.

16:08.480 --> 16:10.600
One of the men was also shot,

16:10.640 --> 16:12.880
and his condition is reported
as serious

16:12.920 --> 16:14.720
but not life-threatening.

16:14.760 --> 16:16.880
The third man, who was only
released from prison

16:16.920 --> 16:18.400
in recent days was --

16:18.440 --> 16:23.040
♪

16:23.080 --> 16:25.200
The third man, who was only
released from prison

16:25.240 --> 16:28.480
in recent days, was not
injured in the shooting.

16:28.520 --> 16:30.280
Gardai are still trying
to establish

16:30.320 --> 16:32.440
a motive
for the shooting,

16:32.480 --> 16:35.280
which is the latest in a series
of gangland incidents...

16:35.320 --> 16:42.120
♪

16:42.160 --> 16:48.640
♪

16:48.680 --> 16:50.960
Jimmy.

16:51.000 --> 16:52.840
Yeah.

16:58.120 --> 17:01.400
I'm disgusted and heartbroken
about what happened.

17:01.440 --> 17:02.960
Yeah.

17:06.840 --> 17:08.600
Amanda said you went
to see Frank.

17:08.640 --> 17:11.000
What's he saying?

17:11.040 --> 17:13.040
You saw Amanda?

17:13.080 --> 17:16.040
Uh, yeah. She --
She called over

17:16.080 --> 17:19.120
'cause she wanted to know what
happened when Jamie was shot.

17:19.160 --> 17:20.480
When was this?

17:20.520 --> 17:22.840
Earlier.

17:22.880 --> 17:25.080
When I got back
from the station.

17:27.320 --> 17:29.080
Is that all
she wanted?

17:29.120 --> 17:31.120
Yeah.

17:32.560 --> 17:34.480
You sure?

17:37.480 --> 17:39.120
Yeah.

17:46.320 --> 17:48.560
Listen, Jimmy --
-I need a drink.

17:48.600 --> 17:50.440
You want a drink?
Let's get a drink.

17:50.480 --> 17:52.720
Sean, can I get a, uh, pint
of Guinness, a whiskey chaser.

17:52.760 --> 17:54.880
Same again
for Michael.

17:57.160 --> 17:58.880
Fuck.
Jimmy, I don't --

17:58.920 --> 18:01.840
Why don't you
get a table?

18:01.880 --> 18:04.440
I'll follow you over.

18:04.480 --> 18:06.800
Go on.

18:06.840 --> 18:09.240
[Footsteps depart]

18:14.200 --> 18:16.520
Amanda'll be looking
for you.

18:16.560 --> 18:19.240
[Chuckles]

18:19.280 --> 18:21.120
Yeah, she made it
pretty fucking clear

18:21.160 --> 18:23.080
she doesn't want
to see me, so...

18:23.120 --> 18:24.360
She's grieving, Jimmy.

18:24.400 --> 18:26.240
Is she?

18:26.280 --> 18:28.240
So am I, Michael.

18:28.280 --> 18:29.720
She doesn't have
the fucking monopoly

18:29.760 --> 18:31.160
on grief,
now, does she?

18:31.200 --> 18:34.240
I know that, but it's different
for a mother.

18:34.280 --> 18:35.880
Wow.

18:39.440 --> 18:41.440
No offense, Michael,
but stay the fuck out

18:41.480 --> 18:43.320
of my marriage, okay?

18:51.800 --> 18:53.680
You see the shooter?

18:55.360 --> 18:56.480
No.

19:00.120 --> 19:02.360
This lad Moore,

19:02.400 --> 19:05.880
he wasn't the triggerman,
but he ordered it.

19:05.920 --> 19:08.920
You don't know him,
but he's a mouthy little prick.

19:08.960 --> 19:10.760
Drink up there.

19:10.800 --> 19:13.280
Drink up.

19:13.320 --> 19:15.640
He'll be keeping
his head down low,

19:15.680 --> 19:17.840
but everyone gets sloppy,
and when he does,

19:17.880 --> 19:20.280
we will be waiting
for him.

19:20.320 --> 19:24.040
Well, I can't be involved
in any of that...

19:24.080 --> 19:25.920
not if I want
to see Anna.

19:25.960 --> 19:27.640
Okay?

19:29.640 --> 19:30.840
What about Jamie?

19:30.880 --> 19:33.440
Doesn't he count?

19:33.480 --> 19:35.440
Fuck you, Michael.

19:35.480 --> 19:37.720
You done it before for money.
Do it now for family.

19:37.760 --> 19:45.800
♪

19:45.840 --> 19:48.440
Claire:
Why isn't Jimmy here?

19:48.480 --> 19:51.080
He's gone to the hospital,
to see Eric. Is that okay?

19:51.120 --> 19:53.600
I'm just surprised
he's not here.

19:53.640 --> 19:57.520
Do you have any idea about, um,
funeral arrangements yet?

19:57.560 --> 19:58.840
Not yet.

19:58.880 --> 20:00.760
Well, we'll need
to let people know soon.

20:00.800 --> 20:01.920
So they can make plans.

20:01.960 --> 20:04.520
I don't know, Mam.

20:04.560 --> 20:07.440
I've said I don't know,
and I don't know.

20:07.480 --> 20:11.280
It's been on the news all day,
about the shooting.

20:11.320 --> 20:13.560
Everyone will know
exactly what happened.

20:13.600 --> 20:16.400
I'm sorry if your grandson's
murder is an embarrassment.

20:16.440 --> 20:18.440
That's not what
your mother's saying.

20:18.480 --> 20:20.400
Yeah, well, then what
areyou saying, Mam?

20:20.440 --> 20:22.480
Just that it was on the news,
that's all.

20:24.840 --> 20:27.120
About everything.
-What's everything?

20:27.160 --> 20:29.040
Eh, w-we didn't come here
to have a fight.

20:29.080 --> 20:32.280
No, no. No.
What is "everything," Mam?

20:32.320 --> 20:35.680
Just about Jimmy
and his family...

20:35.720 --> 20:38.120
and all that business.

20:38.160 --> 20:42.080
Jamie had nothing to
do with any of that.

20:42.120 --> 20:45.160
He didn't deserve
what happened to him.

20:45.200 --> 20:47.080
No one is saying
he deserved it, love.

20:47.120 --> 20:48.560
If that's
the kind of people

20:48.600 --> 20:50.480
he's hanging around with,
what do you expect?

20:50.520 --> 20:53.520
"The kind of people"?

20:53.560 --> 20:56.160
They're his family, Mam.

20:56.200 --> 20:58.240
That doesn't
make it any better.

21:01.240 --> 21:03.080
You know what?
Fuck this.

21:03.120 --> 21:09.200
♪

21:09.240 --> 21:15.320
♪

21:15.360 --> 21:18.400
[Breathing heavily]

21:18.440 --> 21:27.920
♪

21:27.960 --> 21:30.240
[Car door closes]

21:30.280 --> 21:38.400
♪

21:38.440 --> 21:40.360
[Machinery humming]

21:40.400 --> 21:46.200
♪

21:46.240 --> 21:52.000
♪

21:52.040 --> 21:54.640
[Breathing heavily]

21:54.680 --> 22:03.560
♪

22:03.600 --> 22:05.840
[Breathing shakily]

22:05.880 --> 22:08.880
[Sobbing]

22:14.680 --> 22:16.360
[Sniffles]

22:18.480 --> 22:19.720
[Sniffles]

22:19.760 --> 22:22.240
[Breathing shakily]

22:25.200 --> 22:26.960
[Sniffles]

22:31.720 --> 22:34.240
[Sobbing]

22:39.640 --> 22:41.480
[Inhales deeply]

22:41.520 --> 22:43.840
[Exhaling deeply]

22:43.880 --> 22:47.040
[Horn honking]

22:50.160 --> 22:53.240
Fucking move,
you dowsy cunt!

22:53.280 --> 22:56.880
Fuck you! Fuck you!

22:56.920 --> 22:59.360
[Sniffles]

22:59.400 --> 23:02.400
[Breathing heavily]

23:02.440 --> 23:04.360
[Sniffles]

23:04.400 --> 23:12.080
♪

23:12.120 --> 23:15.560
[Engine accelerating]

23:15.600 --> 23:18.120
[Engine revving]

23:18.160 --> 23:20.760
[Horn blaring]

23:20.800 --> 23:24.640
[Indistinct conversations]

23:27.760 --> 23:29.240
Do you think
I'm gonna look like that?

23:29.280 --> 23:30.840
-No.
-She's 54.

23:30.880 --> 23:32.440
Fucking hell.

23:36.240 --> 23:37.760
There you are.

23:37.800 --> 23:38.920
We tried to call you,
let you know

23:38.960 --> 23:41.040
that Eric was awake.

23:41.080 --> 23:42.520
You lied to me.

23:42.560 --> 23:44.320
What?

23:44.360 --> 23:45.560
You looked me in the eye
and told me you had

23:45.600 --> 23:47.440
nothing to do
with that shooting.

23:47.480 --> 23:51.160
-And I didn't.
-Don't fucking lie to me.

23:53.160 --> 23:55.560
And you backed him up.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.920
Look...

23:57.960 --> 24:01.320
[sighs]
he's a fucking prick.

24:01.360 --> 24:03.200
He had it coming.

24:03.240 --> 24:06.120
Your cousin is dead
'cause of what you did.

24:06.160 --> 24:07.920
You know that, don't you?

24:07.960 --> 24:11.640
I couldn't have known that
Jamie'd get caught up in this.

24:11.680 --> 24:15.680
That's Moore's doing, and you
should be fucking out there,

24:15.720 --> 24:18.080
trying to get him instead
of in here, giving me grief.

24:18.120 --> 24:19.760
Shut the fuck up!

24:21.480 --> 24:25.240
I spent the day out
trying to clean up your shit,

24:25.280 --> 24:27.080
at least the parts
that canbe cleaned,

24:27.120 --> 24:30.080
and to tell you, fuck,
the way I am feeling right now,

24:30.120 --> 24:33.000
I would happily
fucking hammer you

24:33.040 --> 24:37.360
right fucking here,
hospital bed or not.

24:39.800 --> 24:41.880
Now, I don't care what
people think they know.

24:43.760 --> 24:46.160
You're asked about
shooting that lad,

24:46.200 --> 24:48.720
you deny it,
especially to Jimmy.

24:48.760 --> 24:50.520
He's gonna find out
eventually.

24:50.560 --> 24:53.840
Maybe. But right now,
he's out gunning for blood,

24:53.880 --> 24:56.000
and I don't want it
to be yours he goes after.

24:58.320 --> 25:00.400
So, you tell no one,
not even Birdy.

25:00.440 --> 25:02.600
Do you understand?

25:02.640 --> 25:05.480
Same goes for you.
-Okay, Frank.

25:05.520 --> 25:07.920
I don't want to hear another
fucking peep about Caolan Moore.

25:07.960 --> 25:10.680
It's done. It's over.

25:10.720 --> 25:13.360
You see him, you cross
the fucking street.

25:13.400 --> 25:15.240
Jimmy tries to talk you
into going after him,

25:15.280 --> 25:18.480
you say no and you come
and tell me.

25:18.520 --> 25:19.760
Is that clear?

25:21.760 --> 25:23.240
Yeah.

25:24.560 --> 25:28.040
[Metal creaking]

25:29.640 --> 25:33.680
[Beeping]

25:33.720 --> 25:43.640
♪

25:43.680 --> 25:45.200
[Whirring]

25:45.240 --> 25:48.040
[Radio chatter]

25:48.080 --> 25:52.000
♪

25:52.040 --> 25:54.240
Jimmy: You sure you don't
want to go to the hospital?

25:54.280 --> 25:56.360
Amanda: I'm fine.

25:58.040 --> 26:00.920
You might still
be in shock.

26:00.960 --> 26:03.760
I'm fine.
I already told you.

26:03.800 --> 26:05.840
Alright.

26:07.920 --> 26:10.760
I've been thinking
about the funeral.

26:10.800 --> 26:14.160
I just want family
and close friends at it.

26:14.200 --> 26:18.080
I don't want a big, fancy thing
and none of that other stuff.

26:20.760 --> 26:23.280
Okay.

26:23.320 --> 26:25.760
I mean it, Jimmy.

26:25.800 --> 26:29.640
I don't want Fudge or Kem
or any of them showing up at it.

26:29.680 --> 26:33.040
They'll want to
pay their respects.

26:33.080 --> 26:36.080
They didn't
even know Jamie.

26:36.120 --> 26:38.240
They'll think it looks bad
if they don't show their faces.

26:38.280 --> 26:40.240
I don't care
what they think.

26:40.280 --> 26:43.320
They're not using
my son's funeral

26:43.360 --> 26:45.960
as an excuse to strut around
and play gangsters.

26:48.480 --> 26:51.600
I just want family
and close friends only.

26:51.640 --> 26:53.920
No one else.

26:53.960 --> 26:56.280
No one.

26:56.320 --> 26:58.240
Okay.

26:59.800 --> 27:02.560
[Cellphone rings]

27:02.600 --> 27:03.800
[Cellphone beeps]

27:03.840 --> 27:05.760
-Frank?
-Yeah.

27:05.800 --> 27:07.360
Where are you now?

27:07.400 --> 27:10.200
In the car.
We're almost home.

27:10.240 --> 27:13.520
You and Michael come and see me
when you get back, yeah?

27:13.560 --> 27:15.160
Why? What's up?

27:15.200 --> 27:17.160
Nothing. I'll fill you in
when I see you.

27:28.240 --> 27:30.160
Why does this feel
like an ambush?

27:30.200 --> 27:33.560
I met Eamon Cunningham
earlier.

27:33.600 --> 27:35.160
Yeah? And?

27:35.200 --> 27:37.120
Caolan Moore's
off-limits.

27:40.960 --> 27:43.280
No.

27:43.320 --> 27:45.640
Frank, no.

27:45.680 --> 27:48.320
That's bollocks.

27:48.360 --> 27:51.360
Moore's not getting away
with this. He's fucking not.

27:51.400 --> 27:53.240
We can't go to war
with Eamon Cunningham.

27:53.280 --> 27:55.840
"We"? They're the ones
that attacked us.

27:55.880 --> 27:58.760
They fucking started this.

27:58.800 --> 28:01.120
Frank, they killed Jamie.

28:01.160 --> 28:03.160
He had nothing to do
with any of this.

28:03.200 --> 28:06.160
It was an accident,
okay?

28:06.200 --> 28:07.560
They didn't mean
to shoot him.

28:07.600 --> 28:09.520
I don't care.

28:09.560 --> 28:11.320
I don't fucking care.
They did it.

28:13.080 --> 28:15.320
Who did they mean
to shoot, Frank?

28:15.360 --> 28:16.560
-Eric.
-Eric?

28:16.600 --> 28:18.520
Your boy?

28:18.560 --> 28:20.040
Why aren't you angry
about that?

28:20.080 --> 28:23.560
I am fucking angry.
We just can't hit back.

28:23.600 --> 28:25.240
Why not?

28:25.280 --> 28:26.720
You know why not.

28:26.760 --> 28:28.120
If it's us
against Eamon,

28:28.160 --> 28:30.480
there's only gonna be
one outcome.

28:30.520 --> 28:33.000
And half the gangs in Dublin
would be queuing up

28:33.040 --> 28:38.440
to do his killing for him...
and take over our business.

28:38.480 --> 28:40.840
Frank is right, Jimmy.

28:43.200 --> 28:45.240
So, you're --
you're okay with all this?

28:45.280 --> 28:47.320
Of course
I'm not okay with it.

28:47.360 --> 28:49.040
But I don't see
that we have a choice.

28:49.080 --> 28:51.520
There's always
a fucking choice.

28:51.560 --> 28:54.160
They're shitting on us,
and we're letting them.

28:54.200 --> 28:56.480
It's fucking embarrassing.
-You're upset.

28:56.520 --> 28:58.720
Just give it time,
wait till all this calms down.

28:58.760 --> 29:00.840
We will get Caolan Moore.
I promise.

29:00.880 --> 29:02.800
When will that be?

29:02.840 --> 29:04.480
A year?

29:04.520 --> 29:07.880
No. No.

29:15.840 --> 29:17.680
This is from Eamon.

29:17.720 --> 29:19.760
For what happened.

29:26.080 --> 29:28.600
Wow.

29:28.640 --> 29:30.600
How much is in there?

29:30.640 --> 29:32.240
Frank:
About 150 grand.

29:32.280 --> 29:34.480
[Laughs]

29:39.440 --> 29:42.200
What am I supposed to
do with this, Frank?

29:42.240 --> 29:46.200
Buy a fucking boat,
go on a holiday,

29:46.240 --> 29:48.280
make up
for Jamie's death?

29:48.320 --> 29:50.560
Is that it?

29:50.600 --> 29:53.080
So, that's it, then? I don't
get a say in the decision?

29:53.120 --> 29:55.840
That's it?
-There's no decision.

29:57.880 --> 30:00.760
We can't go up against
Eamon Cunningham.

30:00.800 --> 30:03.280
Frank's just doing
what's best for everyone.

30:03.320 --> 30:04.840
Jimmy: Yeah.

30:12.760 --> 30:14.360
[Zipper unzips]

30:14.400 --> 30:16.040
Oh, geez.

30:21.600 --> 30:23.960
[Urinating]

30:36.800 --> 30:39.440
[Urinating stops]

30:39.480 --> 30:41.520
[Zipper zips]

30:43.760 --> 30:48.440
♪

30:48.480 --> 30:51.200
Give this back to Eamon for me,
will you, Frank?

30:51.240 --> 30:55.280
♪

30:55.320 --> 30:57.440
[Door opens, closes]

30:59.040 --> 31:01.840
No one wants this, Mikey,
but we have no choice.

31:04.960 --> 31:06.600
I'm gonna go.

31:06.640 --> 31:13.480
♪

31:13.520 --> 31:15.440
[Door opens, closes]

31:17.760 --> 31:18.800
[Ice rattles]

31:20.760 --> 31:24.120
What did Frank want?

31:24.160 --> 31:26.480
Nothing. Just business.

31:30.600 --> 31:32.560
Was it about Jamie?

31:32.600 --> 31:34.160
No.

31:37.600 --> 31:39.680
What happened to you?

31:39.720 --> 31:43.200
Uh, I-I had a tip
in the car.

31:43.240 --> 31:45.800
But you're okay, though? There's
nothing wrong or anything?

31:45.840 --> 31:47.640
Y-You're not hurt?

31:47.680 --> 31:50.440
No. I'm fine.

31:51.680 --> 31:54.600
Aw, come here.

31:54.640 --> 31:57.720
It's alright.

31:57.760 --> 32:00.800
It's alright to be sad.

32:00.840 --> 32:03.880
We're all sad.

32:03.920 --> 32:06.960
I'm not sad.
I'm angry.

32:09.120 --> 32:12.080
It's alright
to be angry, too.

32:14.800 --> 32:17.840
Come on, hug me.

32:17.880 --> 32:21.600
It'll make me feel better
if you hug me, huh?

32:26.560 --> 32:28.400
Yeah, that's better.

32:30.800 --> 32:32.520
That's much better.

32:40.560 --> 32:43.960
[Train passing]

32:47.360 --> 32:57.320
♪

32:57.360 --> 33:07.320
♪

33:07.360 --> 33:17.320
♪

33:17.360 --> 33:27.360
♪

33:27.400 --> 33:32.680
♪

33:32.720 --> 33:35.200
[Dog barking in distance]

33:38.160 --> 33:41.680
[Engine idling]

33:41.720 --> 33:44.400
[Lock clicks, door opens]

33:44.440 --> 33:46.680
Monica: We really should have
known this earlier
about his release.

33:46.720 --> 33:50.200
It's very unusual
that they didn't --

33:50.240 --> 33:52.360
It's highly likely
he'll try to contact her,

33:52.400 --> 33:55.400
so we will be
on top of that.

33:55.440 --> 33:58.600
It could be very damaging
for her, so we need to --

33:58.640 --> 34:00.400
Anna.

34:00.440 --> 34:01.720
Hey, Anna.

34:01.760 --> 34:04.480
Hi. Come in.
Come sit down.

34:07.720 --> 34:12.280
Monica just dropped in
to have a chat with you.

34:12.320 --> 34:16.160
Anna, we've been informed
by the prison service

34:16.200 --> 34:18.760
that your dad
has just been released.

34:18.800 --> 34:20.960
Has he tried to
contact you, Anna?

34:21.000 --> 34:23.000
-No.
-Good.

34:23.040 --> 34:24.480
'Cause he's not allowed
to contact you

34:24.520 --> 34:26.080
unless he goes
through the courts.

34:26.120 --> 34:27.760
So, if he does try
to make contact,

34:27.800 --> 34:29.840
you need to tell
your grandmother, okay?

34:39.440 --> 34:42.400
♪

34:48.600 --> 34:50.560
[Pounding on door]

34:55.800 --> 34:57.080
[Door closes]

34:57.120 --> 34:58.480
Listen, Michael,

34:58.520 --> 34:59.960
I know this is
absolutely fucking shit

35:00.000 --> 35:01.520
for Jimmy and Amanda.

35:01.560 --> 35:03.040
It's wrong, Frank.

35:03.080 --> 35:06.240
But we are gonna get Moore,
in time.

35:06.280 --> 35:09.160
Yeah.
It's like Birdy said.

35:09.200 --> 35:11.440
We just need
to be patient.

35:11.480 --> 35:14.040
And what if that had been
Eric killed, instead of Jamie?

35:14.080 --> 35:16.040
I'd be saying
the exact same thing.

35:16.080 --> 35:18.040
But it wasn't Eric.

35:18.080 --> 35:19.600
And Jamie's not your kid,
either.

35:22.240 --> 35:24.640
Anna is, though.

35:24.680 --> 35:26.560
And no court is gonna let you
anywhere near her

35:26.600 --> 35:29.080
if this family
is in a feud.

35:29.120 --> 35:32.280
Look, I'm staying
out of it.

35:32.320 --> 35:35.800
Yeah. You see if you can
make sure that Jimmy

35:35.840 --> 35:38.320
doesn't do anything...

35:38.360 --> 35:41.880
fucking stupid
in the meantime.

35:41.920 --> 35:44.560
Can you do that?

35:44.600 --> 35:46.440
Mm.

35:46.480 --> 35:47.960
Good.

35:52.040 --> 35:55.080
So, we do nothing?
Like, nothing at all?

35:55.120 --> 35:56.720
Isn't that just
what I fucking said?

35:56.760 --> 35:59.040
This coming
from Frank?

35:59.080 --> 36:01.080
It's coming from me.

36:01.120 --> 36:03.920
Why?

36:03.960 --> 36:06.720
'Cause that's
what was decided.

36:06.760 --> 36:10.360
Look, I know Frank said
that this shit is done,

36:10.400 --> 36:13.600
but the only name we're hearing
around this is Moore's.

36:13.640 --> 36:17.560
Yeah. He's even saying he
put manners on you, bro,

36:17.600 --> 36:20.120
and you're gonna do
fuck all about it.

36:20.160 --> 36:22.480
We need to do something,
even if it's just for show.

36:22.520 --> 36:23.960
No!

36:24.000 --> 36:26.200
It's fucking finished.

36:26.240 --> 36:27.720
Right?

36:27.760 --> 36:30.280
Forget Moore.

36:30.320 --> 36:33.040
And what about Jimmy?
He's not gonna let this go.

36:33.080 --> 36:34.800
He is! We all are!

36:34.840 --> 36:37.200
Because that's what
was decided, right?

36:37.240 --> 36:39.480
Now, I'm bored of explaining
this to the both of you.

36:39.520 --> 36:41.320
It's over.

36:41.360 --> 36:43.520
Fucking end of.

36:43.560 --> 36:45.240
[Scoffs]

36:47.200 --> 36:49.200
Hey, lad's,
visiting time's over.

36:49.240 --> 36:51.960
Alright?
We should go, let you rest.

36:53.720 --> 36:55.560
-Later, V.
-Yeah.

36:55.600 --> 36:57.120
See youse later, yeah?

36:57.160 --> 36:59.480
Look, I'll be back
in the morning, yeah?

36:59.520 --> 37:02.880
And if you need anything,
message me.

37:06.600 --> 37:07.960
Love you.

37:16.920 --> 37:26.880
♪

37:26.920 --> 37:36.840
♪

37:36.880 --> 37:46.800
♪

37:46.840 --> 37:56.880
♪

37:56.920 --> 38:06.880
♪

38:06.920 --> 38:16.800
♪

38:16.840 --> 38:26.840
♪

38:26.880 --> 38:36.880
♪

38:36.920 --> 38:42.320
[Both breathing heavily]

38:42.360 --> 38:52.080
♪

38:54.160 --> 38:55.400
Hey.

38:55.440 --> 38:58.760
[Crying]

38:58.800 --> 39:07.440
♪

39:07.480 --> 39:15.920
♪

39:15.960 --> 39:18.000
You ready to order?

39:18.040 --> 39:22.040
Yeah.
Um, redbreast 12, neat.

39:22.080 --> 39:26.120
Is there, uh,
anything else I can get you?

39:26.160 --> 39:28.520
[Indistinct conversations]

40:34.120 --> 40:36.120
[Sniffles]

40:39.200 --> 40:41.240
Mam.

40:41.280 --> 40:43.160
Mrs. Kinsella.

41:01.000 --> 41:04.320
Um, Donal said if I got a job
and I stayed out of trouble,

41:04.360 --> 41:06.400
I'd have a good chance
of seeing her.

41:09.840 --> 41:11.720
Well, I'm going to be
honest with you --

41:11.760 --> 41:14.640
this is not going
to be straightforward.

41:14.680 --> 41:17.840
Well, Donal Creehan specializes
in criminal law, not family law.

41:17.880 --> 41:20.160
